they like their base R. They like creating the functions themselves, not using the packages. So,

00:12:28.320 --> 00:12:33.119
that has given me a sense of how it's evolved since the beginning of R at Census to now.

00:12:34.320 --> 00:12:39.200
But anyway, so I came, and I, like I said, I asked for an SPSS license. They told me that it was

00:12:39.200 --> 00:12:45.039
really SAS. It was SAS or nothing. So, I took a bunch of SAS classes. I never got the hang of it,

00:12:45.039 --> 00:12:48.159
